#Tulip Mania
Netherlands, 1634-1637

#South Sea Bubble
Great Britain, 1720

#Mississippi Bubble
France, 1720

Long depression (1873-1896): USA + Europe
Great depression (1929-1939): worldwide

Japanese asset price bubble (1986-1991)
Black Monday (1987): stock market crash
Black Wednesday (19992): British pound not able to keep its exchange rate (George Soros)

Dot-com bubble (1995-2000): Internet-related companies

Enron accounting scandal, 2001
MCI Worldcom accounting scandal, 2002

Great recession (2007-2009): worldwide

#Cryptocurrency bubble (2017-2022): bitcoin, altcoins, stablecoins
